bio: The PINPOINT study aims to improve outcomes of patients with lung cancer by diagnosing as early as possible. Within our group, I will focus my research on the implementation of AI, determining the cost-effectiveness of AI tools and showing the carbon footprint when using these innovative solutions.
Next to my work at AstraZeneca, where I am responsible for our thoracic oncology portfolio, I aim to improve lives of lung cancer patients with this PhD


interests:
  - Value of Computer Assisted Detection of incidental pulmonary nodules for early lung cancer detection
- Cost-effectiveness of AI in clinical practice
- Carbon footprint of AI in clinical practice


